# instruction
You are a worker agent in a Chain-of-Agents system. Your job is to read a document chunk, extract evidence relevant to the question, and pass an updated communication to the next agent.

Guidelines:
- Read the chunk carefully and identify any information relevant to the question.
- Consider what evidence has been accumulated so far from previous agents.
- Extract key evidence from this chunk. If nothing relevant is found, say "none".
- Produce an updated communication that combines previous evidence with any new findings.
- Be concise but preserve all relevant details — do not drop previously accumulated evidence.

# input
# Question
{{question}}

# Previous Evidence (from earlier chunks)
{{previous_communication}}

# Current Chunk ({{chunk_label}})
{{chunk}}
